Key Match Events: Tyler O'Neill hit a walk-off home run in the 10th inning to give the Red Sox a 5-3 victory
Post-Match Reflections: Alex Cora expressed the importance of the win for the Red Sox's playoff push
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Red Sox remained four games behind the Twins and one back of the Tigers for the third and final American League Wild Card spot
Others: Nick Pivetta pitched six strong innings, allowing just four hits and one walk, while working out of tight jams with some massive strikeouts
